detaileddescription.para: BME680 configuration macros Enable or un-comment the macro to provide floating point data output BME680 General config
Ambient humidity shift value for compensation
Run gas enable and disable settings
Bit position definitions for sensor settings
Array Index to Field data mapping for Calibration Data

This max value is used to provide precedence to multiplication or division in pressure compensation equation to achieve least loss of precision and avoiding overflows. i.e Comparing value, BME680_MAX_OVERFLOW_VAL = INT32_C(1 << 30)

Macro to SET and GET BITS of a register

detaileddescription.para:
Generic communication function pointer
dev_id
Place holder to store the id of the device structure Can be used to store the index of the Chip select or I2C address of the device.
reg_addr
Used to select the register the where data needs to be read from or written to.
[in/out]
reg_data: Data array to read/write
len
Length of the data array

Delay function pointer
period
Time period in milliseconds
